    "brand": "nasher_miles",
    "star": null,
    "review_title": "",
    "body": "The zipper on my trolley completely failed within just four months of purchase, making it impossible to close and turning the entire trip into a mess. For a so-called “reputed” brand, this is unacceptable. Any decent brand would replace the product or offer a refund under a one-year warranty, especially when the customer is staying abroad. Instead, Nasher Miles has shown zero efficiency, zero accountability, and absolutely no concern for customer experience. Their support is cheap, slow, and outright dismissive. This is easily one of the worst post-purchase experiences I’ve had. In comparison, MOKOBARA is miles ahead in terms of product quality and customer service. Nasher Miles has completely lost my trust — never buying this low-quality trolley again.",
    "date_str": "Reviewed in India on 23 January 2026",
    "verified": true,
    "helpful_votes": null,
    "scraped_at": "2026-04-02T17:26:08.688273Z"
  },
